The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump on June 10, 2019, at the White House. The President congratulated Simon Pagenaud, the winner of the Indianapolis 500, and praised his racing skills. He also commended Roger Penske, the owner of Team Penske, for his success in the racing industry. The President discussed his admiration for NASCAR and the support he received from the organization during his campaign. Additionally, he expressed condolences for the helicopter accident in New York and mentioned ongoing discussions with Mexico regarding tariffs and immigration. The President dismissed John Dean's testimony and defended himself against impeachment inquiries, stating that he had done nothing wrong. He concluded by highlighting the strong state of the U.S. economy and military.